REST APIs is also called RESTFUL APIs
REST = Representational state transfer
API = application programming interface

Rest is a set of architectural constraints , not a protocol or a standard.
API developers can implement REST in a varity of ways

. so hence the REST API is an application programming interface that follows
  the constraints of REST architectural style and allow for interaction with 
  RESTful web services



REST API work on http protocal (this is means whatever operations are accepted by http should be followed by rest api)
** delivers information using any one of the following formats
 * JSON (most popular)
 * text
 * html
 * xml 
 * javascript and more 
